    "title": "Manufacturing Engineer - Reckitt India Holdings Services - Top MNC",
    "description": "We at Reckitt India Holdings Services are looking for an experienced Manufacturing Engineer based out of Delhi. If you are a result-oriented professional with a passion for excellence, we want to hear from you.\n\nAbout Reckitt India Holdings Services:\nReckitt India Holdings Services is a leading organization in the Hybrid sector, committed to excellence, innovation, and employee growth. We offer a dynamic work environment where talent is recognized and rewarded.\n\nKey Responsibilities:\n• Implement lean manufacturing and continuous improvement initiatives\n• Ensure product quality meets internal and customer specifications\n• Implement 5S, Kaizen, and Six Sigma practices on the shop floor\n• Conduct root cause analysis for quality rejections and defects\n• Train and supervise shop floor workers and supervisors\n• Maintain accurate production records and prepare daily reports\n• Coordinate with design and engineering teams on product improvements\n\nRequired Skills & Qualifications:\n• B.Arch / M.Arch from recognized institution\n• 10-15 years of relevant experience\n• Proficiency in Kaizen\n• Proficiency in AutoCAD\n• Proficiency in Lean Manufacturing\n• Proficiency in GD&T\n• Proficiency in ERP Systems\n• Proficiency in SolidWorks\n• Proficiency in Statistical Process Control\n• Proficiency in PLC/SCADA\n\nWork Mode: Hybrid - Flexible work-from-home and office\n\nWhat We Offer:\n• Flexible working hours\n• Provident Fund and Gratuity as per company policy\n• Modern office with recreational facilities\n• Annual performance appraisal\n• Mobile and internet reimbursement\n• Comprehensive health insurance for self and family\n• Salary Range: 20 LPA - 40 LPA per annum\n\nLocation: Delhi, Delhi, India\n\nIf you are excited about this opportunity, apply now and take the next step in your career journey with Reckitt India Holdings Services!",
